<task id="tq05vlnfgxqs" xml:lang="en-US">
    <title>Running the build slave</title>
    <prolog>
        <author>claude</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>
                    Open a Windows command line and go to the
                    <filepath>C:\dita-op</filepath>
                    folder.
                </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>
                    Enter the
                    <userinput>
                        slave
                        <varname>projname</varname>
                    </userinput>
                    command where
                    <varname>projname</varname>
                    is the name of the project for which you want the
                    build to run.
                </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>
                    To stop the slave you will have to type the
                    <userinput>Ctrl-C</userinput>
                    key combination.
                </cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>
            The build slave will run periodically whenever something
            changed in the Subversion repository. See
            <xref href="http://bitten.edgewall.org/" format="html"
                scope="external">The Bitten project</xref>
            for more information about Bitten and the build slave.
        </result>
    </taskbody>
</task>